isn't it?

90
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:00,801
Doing whatever together.

91
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:03,261
What the‐‐the logs up
to yesterday are gone.

92
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:05,222
Is this some kind of glitch?

93
00:05:05,222 --> 00:05:07,808
Whatever.
See you later!

94
00:05:20,612 --> 00:05:21,863
‐ [gasps]

95
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:28,745
Dr. Kishitani!

96
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:29,871
She's awake!

97
00:05:29,871 --> 00:05:31,790
‐ [grunting]

98
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:35,460
<i>[gentle piano music]</i>

99
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,128
Hmm.
Mm‐hmm.

100
00:05:37,128 --> 00:05:40,549
Good.
Your color's looking better.

101
00:05:40,549 --> 00:05:42,676
You don't have any place
that hurts, do you?

102
00:05:42,676 --> 00:05:44,469
Like a sore throat,
or a tummy‐ache,

103
00:05:44,469 --> 00:05:45,470
or anything like that?

104
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:47,305
You're fine?

105
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:50,392
‐ Here.
‐ Hey, that smells tasty.

106
00:05:50,392 --> 00:05:51,810
You've been a big help.

107
00:05:51,810 --> 00:05:53,395
Thanks a lot for staying.

108
00:05:53,395 --> 00:05:54,688
‐ [chuckles]

109
00:05:56,439 --> 00:05:57,691
SHINRA: Come to think of it,

110
00:05:57,691 --> 00:06:00,193
I forgot to tell Celty
about this girl.

111
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:03,530
After bringing Anri over,
Celty rushed out again,

112
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:05,490
like she was busy.

113
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,701
Something about
looking for someone...

114
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:09,911
hmm?

115
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:11,454
Shoo! Shoo!

116
00:06:11,454 --> 00:06:12,998
‐ Uh...

117
00:06:12,998 --> 00:06:16,167
<i>♪ ♪</i>

118
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:18,879
‐ If it's okay with you,
could you tell me your name?

119
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:20,463
‐ It's Akane.

120
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:21,548
‐ Akane, huh?

121
00:06:21,548 --> 00:06:23,300
And your last name?

122
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:24,968
‐ [sighs softly]

123
00:06:24,968 --> 00:06:26,177
‐ That's fine.

124
00:06:26,177 --> 00:06:27,387
Are you all right
with telling me

125
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:28,597
what happened yesterday?

126
00:06:28,597 --> 00:06:29,890
‐ [whimpers]

127
00:06:31,308 --> 00:06:32,350
‐ Please tell me.

128
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:33,643
Why is that you wanted to make

129
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:36,354
the guy with sunglasses go away?

130
00:06:36,354 --> 00:06:38,773
‐ Because he's a hitman.
‐ Uh‐huh?

131
00:06:38,773 --> 00:06:40,358
‐ Uh‐huh.

132
00:06:40,358 --> 00:06:43,403
Somebody told me about him
the other day.

133
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:45,363
He told me a hitman named Shizuo

134
00:06:45,363 --> 00:06:48,116
was going to kill both my dad
and grandfather.

135
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:51,244
But since I can't go back
to my family,

136
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,580
I didn't know what
to do with myself.

137
00:06:54,873 --> 00:06:56,708
‐ Then what about this?

138
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:59,336
Even I can tell that it's
been heavily modified.

139
00:06:59,336 --> 00:07:01,546
‐ It was given to me
since I needed some way

140
00:07:01,546 --> 00:07:02,881
to finish him off.

141
00:07:02,881 --> 00:07:03,923
‐ Who did that?

142
00:07:03,923 --> 00:07:05,383
‐ The same person who taught me

143
00:07:05,383 --> 00:07:06,593
all sorts of things

144
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:07,969
when I first ran away from home.

145
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:09,387
‐ So just to clarify,

146
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:12,307
this person told you about
a hitman named Shizuo?

147
00:07:12,307 --> 00:07:13,892
And he gave you this stun gun?

148
00:07:13,892 --> 00:07:14,893
‐ Mm‐hmm.

149
00:07:14,893 --> 00:07:16,394
‐ [gulps]

150
00:07:16,394 --> 00:07:18,730
What was his name?

151
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:20,357
‐ He said to call him Izaya.

152
00:07:20,357 --> 00:07:22,651
‐ [moans] Forgive me, Celty.

153
00:07:22,651 --> 00:07:25,654
I might be beating you
to the afterlife.

154
00:07:25,654 --> 00:07:27,489
What's with that gentle smile?

155
00:07:27,489 --> 00:07:29,199
I've never seen it before.

156
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:32,243
‐ [laughs]
Just a misunderstanding, Akane.

157
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:33,578
‐ Huh?

158
00:07:33,578 --> 00:07:36,456
‐ Izaya obviously has
the wrong idea about me.

159
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:38,416
I'm no hitman.

160
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:39,584
‐ Is that true?

161
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:41,419
‐ Yeah, it sure is.

162
00:07:41,419 --> 00:07:44,422
Izaya's a friend of mine,
but we had a little falling out

163
00:07:44,422 --> 00:07:45,840
a while back, that's all.

164
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,425
[chuckles]

165
00:07:47,425 --> 00:07:48,760
‐ [laughs nervously]

166
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:51,596
‐ I'll go make up with him
right now.

167
00:07:51,596 --> 00:07:54,599
[whistling]

168
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:56,434
‐ Hey!

169
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:57,769
That Izaya‐‐

170
00:07:57,769 --> 00:07:59,979
is he tired of being alive
or something?

171
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:02,732
TOM: You really
kept it together.

172
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:04,275
That was some act.

173
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:07,112
I think you deserve the People's
Honor Award right now.

174
00:08:07,112 --> 00:08:09,197
‐ Thanks.
I appreciate that.

175
00:08:09,197 --> 00:08:12,242
And Tom, I've got a little favor
I'd like to ask you.

176
00:08:12,242 --> 00:08:13,201
‐ What is it?

177
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:14,494
‐ If stuff goes down today

178
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:16,413
and I get arrested for murder
or worse,

179
00:08:16,413 --> 00:08:18,748
then I want you to make sure
to tell our president

180
00:08:18,748 --> 00:08:20,625
that I was fired yesterday.

181
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:21,710
Can you do that for me?

182
00:08:21,710 --> 00:08:23,294
[elevator dings]

183
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:26,506
[growling]

184
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,675
That's twice you've
wasted my time.

185
00:08:28,675 --> 00:08:30,885
So I'm gonna kill you twice!

186
00:08:31,970 --> 00:08:34,973
[panting]

187
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:37,142
NAMIE: If a painfully obvious
ruse like this one

188
00:08:37,142 --> 00:08:38,476
actually worked on him,

189
00:08:38,476 --> 00:08:41,438
that Shizuo must be
quite the simpleton.

190
00:08:42,439 --> 00:08:44,065
This was such a nuisance.

191
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:45,900
If he can't kill Shizuo
with a knife,

192
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,819
he could use poison
or something.

193
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:49,821
MASAOMI: The guy has a friend.

194
00:08:49,821 --> 00:08:51,656
This friend may be
laughing or crying

195
00:08:51,656 --> 00:08:53,324
or be in some kind of danger.

196
00:08:53,324 --> 00:08:57,162
But all the guy ever does
is run away.

197
00:08:57,162 --> 00:08:58,496
MIKADO: This place is creepy,

198
00:08:58,496 --> 00:08:59,831
and it looks like
it's got roaches.

199
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:02,208
Let's go hang out
a hotel instead.

200
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,461
BOY: They're just roaches.
Eat 'em!

201
00:09:04,461 --> 00:09:06,129
BOY: You eat one.
BOY: [laughing]

202
00:09:06,129 --> 00:09:08,131
BOY: How much will
you pay if I do?

203
00:09:08,131 --> 00:09:10,341
BOY: 300 yen.
BOY: Cheapskate.

204
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:12,761
BOY: I'm game.
BOY: Ugh, for real?

205
00:09:12,761 --> 00:09:14,262
MIKADO: I know this place.

206
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:15,221
BOY: Hey, Aoba.

207
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:16,890
You're driving me crazy.

208
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:18,641
Can I smack him?
‐ Not yet.

209
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:21,478
‐ [giggling]
‐ Uhh!

210
00:09:21,478 --> 00:09:24,522
[all laughing]

211
00:09:29,778 --> 00:09:32,864
CELTY: Mikado?
Why is he here?

212
00:09:36,618 --> 00:09:40,747
‐ I'm sorry, I had to step out
for a minute.

213
00:09:40,747 --> 00:09:42,040
Anything happen?

214
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:44,334
‐ You completed your end
of assignment.

215
00:09:44,334 --> 00:09:46,503
‐ Yes, it was piece of pie.

216
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:48,880
‐ This factory was abandoned
for some time.

217
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:51,341
Is now a hangout for
delinquent boys.

218
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:53,510
‐ Is hangout for
Black Rider, too.

219
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:56,763
I don't understand need to hide
from those kids, though.

220
00:09:56,763 --> 00:09:59,015
‐ Is unclear.
‐ Shall we shoot?

221
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:01,351
‐ It was ineffective yesterday.

222
00:10:01,351 --> 00:10:03,019
That thing is real monster.

223
00:10:03,019 --> 00:10:04,354
If we use sniper rifle,

224
00:10:04,354 --> 00:10:05,897
we'll give away position.

225
00:10:05,897 --> 00:10:07,857
Could be fatal.

226
00:10:07,857 --> 00:10:10,068
‐ Hmm?

227
00:10:10,068 --> 00:10:12,946
‐ When it moves, I will
follow after.

228
00:10:12,946 --> 00:10:14,572
Our target is the girl.

229
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:16,908
The monster may very well
lead us to her.

230
00:10:16,908 --> 00:10:19,869
‐ Sounds as if you're
enjoying this, Verona.

231
00:10:19,869 --> 00:10:21,037
‐ That is affirmative.

232
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:22,914
I am beginning to enjoy myself.

233
00:10:22,914 --> 00:10:24,707
I am quite fond of Ikebukuro.

234
00:10:24,707 --> 00:10:27,836
Half despair, half jealousy.

235
00:10:27,836 --> 00:10:29,129
A dash of hope.

236
00:10:29,129 --> 00:10:31,589
In other words, that's love.

237
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:34,092
‐ Last night, you were hanging
out on the Dollars' member site

238
00:10:34,092 --> 00:10:36,469
asking around about some stuff,
weren't you?

239
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:39,389
You know, about the Dollar's
feud with the guys from Saitama.

240
00:10:39,389 --> 00:10:42,225
‐ Uh, mm, I was looking into it.

241
00:10:42,225 --> 00:10:43,768
Something was bugging me.

242
00:10:43,768 --> 00:10:46,521
‐ I actually happen to know
everything about it.

243
00:10:46,521 --> 00:10:47,981
‐ [gasps] Are you serious?

244
00:10:47,981 --> 00:10:49,440
‐ Yeah, we're the ones
who did it.

245
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:52,443
‐ Huh?
‐ It wasn't a big deal, really.

246
00:10:52,443 --> 00:10:54,612
Me and all the guys here...
[laughter]

247
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:56,239
Acting as members
of the Dollars,

248
00:10:56,239 --> 00:10:58,908
we went over to Saitama
and attacked that gang.

249
00:10:58,908 --> 00:11:00,785
‐ Uh, what's that?

250
00:11:00,785 --> 00:11:03,788
‐ You know those guys calling
themselves the Toramaru?

251
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:05,123
Remember the other day?

252
00:11:05,123 --> 00:11:07,292
They were chasing after us
in Kadota's van,

253
00:11:07,292 --> 00:11:08,793
and that person
on the Black Bike.

254
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:10,795
‐ Uh, yeah, what about it?

255
00:11:10,795 --> 00:11:12,046
‐ When we were down in Saitama,

256
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:13,965
we set a bunch of their bikes
on fire.

257
00:11:13,965 --> 00:11:15,175
And while we were at it,

258
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:17,677
we sent about 20 of them
to the hospital.

259
00:11:17,677 --> 00:11:20,054
‐ In other words, you tossed
a Molotov cocktail

260
00:11:20,054 --> 00:11:22,098
into the parking lot where
they were hanging out at,

261
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:23,183
right, Aoba?

262
00:11:23,183 --> 00:11:26,311
‐ Ah, but why?

263
00:11:26,311 --> 00:11:29,564
‐ Funny thing is, we're not
just members of the Dollars.

264
00:11:29,564 --> 00:11:31,733
We've also got another name.

265
00:11:31,733 --> 00:11:33,151
‐ Another name?

266
00:11:33,151 --> 00:11:35,737
‐ [chuckling]
I'm sure you must be familiar

267
00:11:35,737 --> 00:11:37,280
with the Blue Squares.

268
00:11:42,994 --> 00:11:46,497
‐ No way.
‐ I'm being honest with you.

269
00:11:46,497 --> 00:11:48,208
Coming into contact
with a painting

270
00:11:48,208 --> 00:11:51,377
is the same thing as meeting
the girl you're destined for.

271
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:52,670
‐ Yeah?

272
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:54,672
But in my eyes, you're more
of a masterpiece

273
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:57,133
than any painting could ever be.

274
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:58,676
WOMAN: What?!

275
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:00,386
Well, I think any man
who'd buy a painting like this

276
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:02,347
would be considered
God's gift to women.

277
00:12:02,347 --> 00:12:03,723
‐ [laughs] You serious?

278
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:05,934
‐ It's as good as sold.
WOMAN: I really am.

279
00:12:05,934 --> 00:12:07,685
CHIKAGE: Well, then...

280
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:09,479
‐ Yes?

281
00:12:09,479 --> 00:12:11,940
Is there perhaps something
I can assist you with, sir?

282
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:14,609
‐ Yeah, there is, actually,
about this painting over here.

283
00:12:14,609 --> 00:12:17,278
This lady's sort of in a bind
unless it's sold.

284
00:12:17,278 --> 00:12:18,988
And so...

285
00:12:18,988 --> 00:12:19,989
come on.

286
00:12:19,989 --> 00:12:21,157
‐ What?

287
00:12:21,157 --> 00:12:23,493
‐ It costs 1,280,000 yen.

288
00:12:23,493 --> 00:12:25,870
If you don't have cash,
plastic's fine.

289
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:27,872
‐ Huh?
‐ Hey, get with the program.

290
00:12:27,872 --> 00:12:30,041
She said that she'd be
in a bind and everything.

291
00:12:30,041 --> 00:12:32,543
A real man wouldn't let her
go through that.

292
00:12:32,543 --> 00:12:33,836
And you're standing
right there‐‐

293
00:12:33,836 --> 00:12:35,213
a man who clearly has money.

294
00:12:35,213 --> 00:12:38,049
You probably own this gallery,
don't you?

295
00:12:38,049 --> 00:12:40,093
So naturally,
you've got capital.

296
00:12:40,093 --> 00:12:41,469
‐ Well...

297
00:12:41,469 --> 00:12:43,554
‐ You're supposed to use
your money for women.

298
00:12:43,554 --> 00:12:44,514
Everyone knows that.

299
00:12:44,514 --> 00:12:46,015
Now, if you call yourself a man,

300
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:49,644
go on ahead and buy this
painting and help the lady out.

301
00:12:49,644 --> 00:12:52,063
‐ Now, now, sir.
Enough joking.

302
00:12:52,063 --> 00:12:55,608
‐ Joking?
Did you think I was being funny?

303
00:12:55,608 --> 00:12:57,527
When did I make you laugh, huh?

304
00:12:57,527 --> 00:13:00,113
‐ Uh, please,
you don't have to.

305
00:13:00,113 --> 00:13:02,407
‐ Hey, old man.
‐ Yes?

306
00:13:02,407 --> 00:13:05,285
‐ It's obvious that young lady
over there is a hard worker.

307
00:13:05,285 --> 00:13:06,869
So just where the hell
do you get off

308
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:08,079
glaring at her like that?

309
00:13:08,079 --> 00:13:09,998
‐ [gasps]
[cell phone chimes]

310
00:13:09,998 --> 00:13:13,001
‐ Found one?
Where are you?

311
00:13:13,001 --> 00:13:15,586
What?
Which building?

312
00:13:15,586 --> 00:13:17,380
I'll be coming back here
at some point

313
00:13:17,380 --> 00:13:20,425
to check if you actually
bought that painting from her.

314
00:13:20,425 --> 00:13:21,718
Are you serious?

315
00:13:21,718 --> 00:13:23,594
Man, that's right out front.

316
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:28,224
‐ [moaning]

317
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:32,687
‐ So you sure about this?

318
00:13:32,687 --> 00:13:36,024
‐ Yeah, it's a Dollars member
who kind of sticks out.

319
00:13:36,024 --> 00:13:37,400
‐ Where is he right now?

320
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,901
‐ Well, that's the funny thing.

321
00:13:38,901 --> 00:13:40,820
Just before you got here,
a girl called him over

322
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:42,655
and then took him inside
that building.

323
00:13:42,655 --> 00:13:44,115
‐ Wha...?

324
00:13:44,115 --> 00:13:47,035
‐ Well, we are talking
silkscreen here, after all.

325
00:13:47,035 --> 00:13:48,703
At this size,
even with the frame,

326
00:13:48,703 --> 00:13:51,706
the manufacturing cost would
only be 24,000 yen.

327
00:13:51,706 --> 00:13:54,876
Don't get me wrong; I've got
respect for Suzie Yasuda,

328
00:13:54,876 --> 00:13:57,170
so I wouldn't mind paying
a million yen for it.

329
00:13:57,170 --> 00:13:59,672
But if I did, I'd have to have
some kind of proof

330
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:01,049
that at least 800,000 of it

331
00:14:01,049 --> 00:14:02,467
was going to the creator.

332
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:04,260
It wouldn't sit well
with me otherwise.

333
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:05,720
‐ Uh, excuse me, sir?

334
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:07,472
‐ And the truth is that
your explanation of things

335
00:14:07,472 --> 00:14:09,766
has a lot of holes in it‐‐
a lot!

336
00:14:09,766 --> 00:14:13,311
You weren't able to describe
even 1% of Suzie's allure‐‐1!

337
00:14:13,311 --> 00:14:15,480
Listen up‐‐what makes his work
so charming is his‐‐

338
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:16,814
‐ That's quite enough!

339
00:14:16,814 --> 00:14:18,232
I can't believe you're
back here again!

340
00:14:18,232 --> 00:14:20,109
Please leave at once!

341
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:22,320
There's no way you could
have known, since you're new,

342
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:24,113
but that customer's
been blacklisted.

343
00:14:24,113 --> 00:14:26,115
So please, don't solicit
his patronage,

344
00:14:26,115 --> 00:14:28,242
even if he does seem
like an easy mark.

345
00:14:28,242 --> 00:14:29,494
‐ I'm sorry.

346
00:14:29,494 --> 00:14:32,497
‐ [groaning]

347
00:14:32,497 --> 00:14:34,123
I got to get out
of this business.

348
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:35,124
Ugh.

349
00:14:39,504 --> 00:14:41,839
CHIKAGE: Him?
He doesn't look like one.

350
00:14:41,839 --> 00:14:43,341
MAN: Well, from what I hear,

351
00:14:43,341 --> 00:14:45,176
that's the kind of group
the Dollars is.

352
00:14:45,176 --> 00:14:47,553
But I also hear that
a decent amount of our guys

353
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:49,514
got clobbered by one
of his buddies‐‐

354
00:14:49,514 --> 00:14:51,974
a bastard named Kadota.

355
00:14:51,974 --> 00:14:53,935
And that guy seems like
one of the top dogs

356
00:14:53,935 --> 00:14:55,520
in the Dollars or something.

357
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:56,979
‐ Yeah?

358
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:01,609
Oh!

359
00:15:01,609 --> 00:15:03,444
MAN: Hey, that's him.

360
00:15:03,444 --> 00:15:05,905
That's Kadota‐‐the guy
I was talking about.

361
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:07,907
‐ They're with a woman, huh?

362
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:09,325
Let's hold off for now.

363
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:11,119
Just watch them.
‐ Right.

364
00:15:11,119 --> 00:15:12,954
[indistinct murmuring]

365
00:15:12,954 --> 00:15:14,413
GIRL: Can't be this cute...

366
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:16,124
[laughter]

367
00:15:16,124 --> 00:15:19,210
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

368
00:15:19,210 --> 00:15:21,420
<i>♪ ♪</i>

369
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:23,172
‐ I can handle the rest.

370
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:25,049
You go ahead and join
the others.

371
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:27,176
‐ But boss‐‐
‐ Just go already.

372
00:15:27,176 --> 00:15:28,427
‐ Later.

373
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:37,019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

374
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:42,650
‐ What?

375
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:45,695
A girls' school smack
in the middle of Ikebukuro?

376
00:15:45,695 --> 00:15:48,823
[girls giggling]

377
00:15:48,823 --> 00:15:50,616
Oh, right, it's Sunday.

378
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:52,952
But the anticipation's
killing me.

379
00:15:54,245 --> 00:15:56,330
‐ You got some business
with us or something?

380
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:00,751
[laughter]
MIKADO: Why would you do that?

381
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:03,254
Attacking people from Saitama?

382
00:16:03,254 --> 00:16:04,547
That's crazy.

383
00:16:04,547 --> 00:16:06,382
‐ They didn't give me
any choice.

384
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:09,343
After all, they were the ones
who spoiled the Ikebukuro tour

385
00:16:09,343 --> 00:16:11,304
I was going to have
with you and Anri.

386
00:16:11,304 --> 00:16:13,514
So it was payback.

387
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:14,807
Or is that not a good reason?

388
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:16,851
[laughter]
MIKADO: This is insane.

389
00:16:16,851 --> 00:16:19,395
The Blue Squares...

390
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:22,481
a gang Masaomi feuded with.

391
00:16:22,481 --> 00:16:24,525
I've heard of the Blue Squares.

392
00:16:24,525 --> 00:16:25,985
If I remember it right,

393
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:28,237
they were a color gang
from around this area.

394
00:16:28,237 --> 00:16:30,990
And they had a feud
with the Yellow Scarves.

395
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:32,783
‐ Well, you know
a lot more about us

396
00:16:32,783 --> 00:16:34,035
than I would've thought.

397
00:16:34,035 --> 00:16:35,953
I'm impressed, Mikado.

398
00:16:35,953 --> 00:16:39,373
MIKADO: But Masaomi didn't
tell me everything.

399
00:16:39,373 --> 00:16:41,292
‐ Ah, you noticed
I was tailing you.

400
00:16:41,292 --> 00:16:43,169
‐ That's right, though you did
throw me off a little

401
00:16:43,169 --> 00:16:45,421
when you stepped in front
of this girls' school.

402
00:16:45,421 --> 00:16:48,341
You almost made me think that
my intuition was out of whack.

403
00:16:48,341 --> 00:16:51,052
‐ You're a Dollar,
unless I'm mistaken.

404
00:16:51,052 --> 00:16:53,095
‐ Well, I wouldn't argue
with you about that.

405
00:16:53,095 --> 00:16:55,932
‐ I heard Shizuo Heiwajima's
also a Dollar.

406
00:16:55,932 --> 00:16:57,183
Is that true?

407
00:16:57,183 --> 00:16:58,684
‐ I guess you could say
that's true,

408
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:00,353
more or less.

409
00:17:00,353 --> 00:17:03,147
That guy's got almost no clue
of how to be a team player.

410
00:17:03,147 --> 00:17:06,400
‐ Yeah, he does seem
like that type.

411
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,735
[neck cracks]

412
00:17:07,735 --> 00:17:09,654
‐ Well, you got a name,
or what?

413
00:17:09,654 --> 00:17:11,030
[cell phone beeps]
Hmm?

414
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:12,323
CHIKAGE: You can answer that.

415
00:17:12,323 --> 00:17:14,408
I'll wait for you.

416
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:15,701
[chuckles]

417
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:18,412
‐ It's an email.

418
00:17:19,830 --> 00:17:22,250
[phones chiming and beeping]

419
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:24,168
‐ They really are all Dollars.

420
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:27,255
<i>[electric guitar riff]</i>

421
00:17:27,255 --> 00:17:28,464
[gasps]

422
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:30,341
AOBA: Looks like
it's started, huh?

423
00:17:30,341 --> 00:17:31,884
[laughter]

424
00:17:31,884 --> 00:17:34,887
‐ What are you talking about?
What's started?

425
00:17:37,223 --> 00:17:39,684
‐ Toramaru's inevitable revenge.

426
00:17:41,018 --> 00:17:43,813
‐ What's wrong?
‐ You bastard.

427
00:17:43,813 --> 00:17:45,898
What the hell are
you guys up to?

428
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:47,525
‐ I'm Chikage Rokujo,
by the way.

429
00:17:47,525 --> 00:17:49,235
And, hey, I only
came to this town

430
00:17:49,235 --> 00:17:52,029
to get some payback for the
fight that you guys started.

431
00:17:52,029 --> 00:17:53,781
You can keep the change, though,

432
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:55,741
as long as you take this
in full.

433
00:17:58,119 --> 00:18:00,037
[chuckles]

434
00:18:00,037 --> 00:18:01,664
[leaves rustling]

435
00:18:01,664 --> 00:18:03,207
MIKADO: You're the cause
of all this.

436
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:05,376
Why would you do something
like this?

437
00:18:05,376 --> 00:18:08,504
And why did you admit it to me,
out of all people?

438
00:18:08,504 --> 00:18:11,007
AOBA: Because I trust you,
Mikado.

439
00:18:11,007 --> 00:18:13,175
‐ That's no answer at all, Aoba.

440
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:14,677
What do you plan to do with me?

441
00:18:14,677 --> 00:18:16,637
‐ That's a good question.

442
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:18,514
It would've been better
if we'd done this

443
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:21,350
after you had a chance to get
to know us a little more.

444
00:18:21,350 --> 00:18:22,727
But at this point,
we might as well

445
00:18:22,727 --> 00:18:25,229
come right out and ask you.

446
00:18:25,229 --> 00:18:26,856
Be our leader.
[laughter]

447
00:18:26,856 --> 00:18:27,773
‐ What?

448
00:18:27,773 --> 00:18:28,941
‐ I'm not asking you

449
00:18:28,941 --> 00:18:30,568
to become the leader
of the Dollars.

450
00:18:30,568 --> 00:18:32,278
No, that would break
the founding principle

451
00:18:32,278 --> 00:18:33,571
of the Dollars.

452
00:18:33,571 --> 00:18:36,824
[laughter]

453
00:18:36,824 --> 00:18:39,327
So the thing I'm after here,
if you're willing,

454
00:18:39,327 --> 00:18:40,870
is that I'd basically
like you to become

455
00:18:40,870 --> 00:18:42,204
the leader of the Blue Squares.

456
00:18:42,204 --> 00:18:43,623
‐ [gasps]

457
00:18:43,623 --> 00:18:46,626
‐ Generally speaking,
we'll do as you say.

458
00:18:46,626 --> 00:18:49,211
‐ Why? Why me?

459
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:51,422
AOBA: There are a lot of
reasons, to tell you the truth.

460
00:18:51,422 --> 00:18:54,467
But I guess it's because
you hold a special position

461
00:18:54,467 --> 00:18:55,760
in the Dollars.

462
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:56,927
‐ Special position?

463
00:18:56,927 --> 00:18:58,596
AOBA:
To make a long story short,

464
00:18:58,596 --> 00:19:01,223
it's because you're the one
who founded the Dollars.

465
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:02,558
‐ Uh...?

466
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:05,227
[laughter]

467
00:19:05,227 --> 00:19:06,979
‐ Are you surprised that I know?

468
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:08,689
It just shows that we've got
a pretty decent

469
00:19:08,689 --> 00:19:11,359
information‐gathering
network of our own.

470
00:19:11,359 --> 00:19:14,862
<i>[rock music]</i>

471
00:19:14,862 --> 00:19:16,489
‐ Damn that bastard.

472
00:19:16,489 --> 00:19:19,617
I told him to never come back
to Ikebukuro.

473
00:19:19,617 --> 00:19:22,411
And he set up shop
out here in the open!

474
00:19:22,411 --> 00:19:24,872
[doorbell dings]

475
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:27,625
[grunting impatiently]

476
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:30,211
[growling]

477
00:19:30,211 --> 00:19:31,545
Argh!

478
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:32,922
[latch clicks]
Huh?

479
00:19:34,965 --> 00:19:36,926
WOMAN: Oh, really?
I guess it could be.

480
00:19:36,926 --> 00:19:39,470
In your case, it's like,
at home you walk around

481
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:41,555
in the most indecorous manner.

482
00:19:41,555 --> 00:19:43,641
‐ Indecorous? [laughing]

483
00:19:43,641 --> 00:19:45,351
That sounds scandalous.
‐ [snarling]

484
00:19:45,351 --> 00:19:47,353
MAN: It's not as bad
as all that.

485
00:19:47,353 --> 00:19:49,438
Let's just say that I prefer
to unwind in my birthday suit

486
00:19:49,438 --> 00:19:50,981
and leave it at that.

487
00:19:50,981 --> 00:19:53,025
WOMAN: It's like you're
practically a nudist.

488
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:54,402
‐ Who the hell are you?

489
00:19:54,402 --> 00:19:56,987
What's the big idea,
barging in?

490
00:19:56,987 --> 00:19:58,739
Kid?

491
00:19:58,739 --> 00:19:59,990
Bastard!

492
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:03,786
<i>[tense bass music]</i>

493
00:20:03,786 --> 00:20:05,538
Shizuo!

494
00:20:05,538 --> 00:20:06,914
Heiwajima was here.

495
00:20:06,914 --> 00:20:08,124
I just saw him!

496
00:20:08,124 --> 00:20:10,167
Get word out to Mr. Shiki
right now!

497
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:12,002
Shizuo wasted three of our guys!

498
00:20:12,002 --> 00:20:14,338
[television droning]

499
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:16,674
AOBA: You'll be free to use us
in whatever way you want.

500
00:20:16,674 --> 00:20:19,593
If that happens to be
stopping this gang war,

501
00:20:19,593 --> 00:20:21,345
then just go ahead
and give the order.

502
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:24,014
If you tell us to crawl on
our knees to the Toramaru

503
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:25,516
and take a beating,

504
00:20:25,516 --> 00:20:27,184
we'll accept that order.

505
00:20:27,184 --> 00:20:29,854
Then again, if you tell us
to crush them instead,

506
00:20:29,854 --> 00:20:31,856
then we'll go ahead
and do just that,

507
00:20:31,856 --> 00:20:34,358
no matter what it might take.

508
00:20:34,358 --> 00:20:36,527
‐ Doing that‐‐either of those‐‐

509
00:20:36,527 --> 00:20:37,737
it's impossible!

510
00:20:37,737 --> 00:20:39,196
There's no way I could do that!

511
00:20:39,196 --> 00:20:41,574
What in the world made you think
I could ever

512
00:20:41,574 --> 00:20:43,534
take on something like that,

513
00:20:43,534 --> 00:20:45,369
when I want to avoid conflict?

514
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:47,455
All I have to do is
keep my mouth shut

515
00:20:47,455 --> 00:20:49,039
about being a Dollar.

516
00:20:49,039 --> 00:20:51,625
That's the kind of person I am.

517
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:53,294
If you're looking for a leader,

518
00:20:53,294 --> 00:20:55,421
I'm definitely not your guy.

519
00:20:55,421 --> 00:20:57,590
‐ That isn't true at all,
Mikado.

520
00:20:57,590 --> 00:20:58,924
‐ [exhales sharply]

521
00:21:01,218 --> 00:21:03,387
‐ And the thing that proves it

522
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:05,806
is the fact that right now...

523
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:07,349
you're smiling.

524
00:21:09,185 --> 00:21:11,020
[laughter]

525
00:21:11,020 --> 00:21:14,064
<i>[slow dramatic music]</i>

526
00:21:14,064 --> 00:21:17,234
<i>♪ ♪</i>

527
00:21:17,234 --> 00:21:20,738
‐ She said she wanted to come,
so I brought her along.

528
00:21:20,738 --> 00:21:24,366
I wonder if I should have.

529
00:21:24,366 --> 00:21:25,910
Don't worry, Akane.

530
00:21:25,910 --> 00:21:27,953
The people who are supposed
to be meeting us here

531
00:21:27,953 --> 00:21:29,997
are very nice.

532
00:21:29,997 --> 00:21:31,415
‐ [whimpers]

533
00:21:31,415 --> 00:21:38,464
<i>♪ ♪</i>

534
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:42,176
‐ Hey.
‐ Uh?

535
00:21:42,176 --> 00:21:43,719
‐ Is something the matter?

536
00:21:43,719 --> 00:21:47,139
‐ Ah, I just found out that all
the chat logs got deleted.

537
00:21:47,139 --> 00:21:49,892
Maybe there was another storm.

538
00:21:49,892 --> 00:21:53,270
‐ Or maybe everybody
just disappeared.

539
00:21:53,270 --> 00:21:56,148
‐ Don't go all spooky on me.

540
00:21:56,148 --> 00:21:58,067
[sighs]

541
00:21:58,067 --> 00:22:00,110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

542
00:22:00,110 --> 00:22:02,613
‐ [chuckles]

543
00:22:02,613 --> 00:22:04,323
MASAOMI: He just ran and ran,

544
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:07,785
further inside the emptiness
of himself,

545
00:22:07,785 --> 00:22:11,539
wondering if he really
did lose everything.

546
00:22:11,539 --> 00:22:14,750
<i>[eerie music]</i>

547
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:18,754
‐ [chuckling]

548
00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:22,466
[laughter continues]

549
00:22:22,466 --> 00:22:23,676
<i>♪ ♪</i>

550
00:22:28,222 --> 00:22:31,350
<i>["Never Say Never" by</i>
<i>Three Lights Down Kings]</i>

551
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:34,436
[man singing in Japanese]

552
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:41,443
<i>♪ ♪</i>

553
00:23:56,810 --> 00:23:58,395
AKABAYASHI: Everywhere you go,

554
00:23:58,395 --> 00:23:59,396
it's shady.

555
00:23:59,396 --> 00:24:01,315
Everybody's sketchy.

556
00:24:01,315 --> 00:24:03,067
It's always been
that kind of city.

557
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:04,818
But lately, it's getting worse.

558
00:24:04,818 --> 00:24:08,072
Next time: "The Day Is Short,
The Work Is Long."

559
00:24:08,072 --> 00:24:10,699
An ominous smell fills the air.

